    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="185"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/3283</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Swiss
                        Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sulzer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 127</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of January 30, 1918,<note n="1" xml:id="d185fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    in which you requested that arrangements be made to transfer the German subjects
                    now interned at <persName corresp="#p_DEL1">Ellis</persName> Island to Hot
                    Springs, N. C.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that I submitted this matter to the
                    Secretary of Labor, from whom I have now received a reply <pb facs="0275"
                        n="191" xml:id="pg_191"/> stating that the matter of transferring the enemy
                    aliens interned at <persName corresp="#p_DEL1">Ellis</persName> Island, as well
                    as those at Gloucester City, N. J., to Hot Springs, N.C., was under
                    consideration and that he furthermore expected that the transfer would be
                    completed very soon, possibly within the next 10 days.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
